entries.meaning: (baseball, softball) The region of the field between the infield and the outer fence.
examples: He hit a long fly ball to the outfield in the gap to left.

entries.meaning: (cricket) The region of the field roughly outside of the infield or the wicket-keeper, slips, gully, point, cover, mid off, mid on, midwicket and square leg.
The area outside a racetrack or running track.
(Scotland, agriculture) Arable land continually cropped without being manured.
(Scotland, agriculture) Any open field at a distance from the farmsteading.

verbs.description: outfield (third-person singular simple present outfields, present participle outfielding, simple past and past participle outfielded)

entries.meaning: (baseball, cricket) To perform better in defense (fielding).
